description: From over- +‎ battle (“fertile, fruitful”). More at over-, battle.

adjectives.description: overbattle (comparative more overbattle, superlative most overbattle)

entries.meaning: (dialectal or obsolete) Too fertile; too rich.
examples: For in the Church of God sometimes it cometh to pass as in over-battle grounds, the fertile disposition whereof is good. ― Hooker.
